<!--
    COLT JUNIOR (.25 ACP)
    =====================
    Deep concealment "gentleman's gun" - marginal terminal performance

    Real-World Specs:
    - Barrel: 2.25"
    - Weight: 12-13 oz empty
    - Capacity: 6+1
    - Muzzle Velocity: 753-780 fps (50gr FMJ)
    - Muzzle Energy: 63-65 ft-lbs
    - Production: 1958-1973 (~160,000 units)

    Ballistic Notes:
    - .25 ACP operates at 1/5 the energy of 9mm
    - FBI gel: 11-12" penetration, no expansion
    - 35% failure to incapacitate rate (highest of any caliber)
    - Essentially a "better than nothing" caliber

    Game Balance:
    - Damage: 8 (1/5 of 9mm baseline)
    - Very short effective range
    - Minimal recoil (easy follow-up shots)
    - High headshot multiplier to compensate for weak body shots
-->
